PID output, [P value], [I value], [D value] Configure Control Loop PID Values P value The value for P (proportional) I value The value for I (integral) D value The value for D (derivative) Example: PID 1, 10, 50. Control Loop 1 P is 10 and I is 50.

PID output, [P value], [I value], [D value] Configure Control Loop PID Values P value The value for P (proportional) I value The value for I (integral) D value The value for D (derivative) Example: PID 1, 10, 50. Control Loop 1 P is 10 and I is 50.

RAMP output, [off/on], [rate value] Configure Ramp Parameters for specified output off/on Specifies whether ramping is off or on rate value Specifies how many kelvin per minute to ramp the setpoint (0.1 - 100) Example: RAMP 1, 1, 10.5. When the setpoint for output 1 is changed, ramp the current setpoint to the target setpoint at 10.5 K/minute.

RAMP output, [off/on], [rate value] Configure Ramp Parameters for specified output off/on Specifies whether ramping is off or on rate value Specifies how many kelvin per minute to ramp the setpoint (0.1 - 100) Example: RAMP 1, 1, 10.5. When the setpoint for output 1 is changed, ramp the current setpoint to the target setpoint at 10.5 K/minute.

RELAY high/low, mode, input alarm, alarm type Configure Relay Control Parameters for the HIGH relay. mode Specifies relay settings mode. Valid entries: 0:off, 1:on, 2:alarms. input alarm Specifies which input alarm activates the relay when it is in alarm mode (A-D). alarm type Specifies the alarm type that activates the relay. 0:Low alarm, 1:High alarm, 2:Both alarms Example: RELAY 1,2,B,0. Relay 1 (Hi) activates when input B low alarm activates.

RELAY high/low, mode, input alarm, alarm type Configure Relay Control Parameters for the LOW relay mode Specifies relay settings mode. Valid entries: 0:off, 1:on, 2:alarms. input alarm Specifies which input alarm activates the relay when it is in alarm mode (A-D). alarm type Specifies the alarm type that activates the relay. 0:Low alarm, 1:High alarm, 2:Both alarms Example: RELAY 2,2,B,0. Relay 2 (Lo) activates when input B low alarm activates.

*STB? Query Status Byte. The integer returned represents the sum of the bit weighting of the status flag bits that are set in the Status Byte Register. Acts like a serial poll, but does not reset the register to all zeros. Bit Bit Weighting Event Name 0 1 not used 1 2 not used 2 4 not used 3 8 not used 4 16 MAV Message available bit 5 32 ESB Event summary bit 6 64 RQS Request service bit 7 128 OSB Operation summary bit
